cs.NE, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV 

The paper deals with recurrent neural networks and their application to language modeling tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper focuses on natural language processing tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel theoretical analysis of recurrent networks, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper includes experiments on character prediction, which could also place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision).
